5\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"750\" height=\"375\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Switching to dark mode in Microsoft Word web.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-background-toggle-microsoft-word-web.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e If you want to keep the UI dark but maintain the default theme for the document background (black text on a white background), click \u0026#34;Switch Background\u0026#34; in the Dark Mode group of the ribbon. This option will only appear after you enable dark mode.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"750\" height=\"375\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Switching background in Microsoft Word web.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/switch-mode-dark-mode-microsoft-word-windows.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"on-mobile\"\u003e On Mobile \u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChances are if your device is using dark mode in the system settings, Word will default to that as well. But if it isn\u0026#39;t, there are a few ways to change that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn iPhone, there isn\u0026#39;t a toggle to turn on dark mode in Word\u0026#39;s settings. That means to enable it, you\u0026#39;ll have to do it in the system settings by heading to Settings \u0026gt; Display \u0026amp; Brightness and tapping \u0026#34;Dark\u0026#34; to switch Microsoft Word\u0026#39;s UI to dark mode. Keep in mind that this will also affect other apps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1170\" height=\"750\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Setting the display settings to dark mode in iPhone settings.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/dark-mode-display-settings-iphone.PNG\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e When you open the document in the app, you can set the background to use a dark theme. To do that, tap the three-dot icon in the top-right corner and toggle on \u0026#34;Dark Background\u0026#34; in the menu.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1170\" height=\"585\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Switching the background to dark in Microsoft Word on iPhone.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/enable-dark-background-microsoft-word-iphone.PNG\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e On an Android phone, you can enable dark mode without changing the system settings. Tap the profile picture icon in the top-left corner of the screen and select \u0026#34;Settings\u0026#34; in the menu.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_27\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe used a Samsung phone for the instructions here. The steps might be different depending on the Android device you are using.\u003c/p\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1080\" height=\"540\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Navigating to settings in Microsoft Word on Android.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/setttings-microsoft-word-android.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e In the Display Preferences section, tap the “Light” option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1080\" height=\"540\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"The display preferences in the Microsoft Word app on Android.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/display-preferences-light-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Then, tap “Dark” in the menu to enable dark mode.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1076\" height=\"550\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Switching to dark mode in the Microsoft Word app on Android.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/toggle-dark-mode-microsoft-word-android.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e If the document background is light, tap the three-dot icon in the top-right corner and tap \u0026#34;Switch Document Background\u0026#34; in the menu.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen you enable dark mode in Microsoft Word on one platform, it will not affect the others—you\u0026#39;ll have to do it manually on each. Also, it will not affect how your document will look in print (you can verify this in Print Preview). So you don\u0026#39;t have worry about enabling it if you don\u0026#39;t want any of those things to happen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are some \u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/812186/dark-mode-is-overrated-and-heres-why/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003epotential drawbacks to using dark mode\u003c/a\u003e. However, I find that the benefits—a vastly superior visual experience—outweigh the downsides. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
